  "url": "https://www.ada.lk/breaking_news/\u0dc4\u0ddc\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0db1\u0dca\u0d9c\u0dda-\u0d86\u0dbb\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc2\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0da7-\u0da2\u0db1\u0dcf\u0db0\u0dd2\u0db4\u0dad\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dbb\u0dba\u0dd9\u0d9a\u0dca-\u0db4\u0dad\u0dca-\u0d9a\u0dbb\u0dbd\u0dcf/11-395626",
  "time_ut": 1658398539,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0dc4\u0ddc\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0db1\u0dca\u0d9c\u0dda \u0d86\u0dbb\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc2\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0da7 \u0da2\u0db1\u0dcf\u0db0\u0dd2\u0db4\u0dad\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dbb\u0dba\u0dd9\u0d9a\u0dca \u0db4\u0dad\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dbb\u0dbd\u0dcf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A president has been appointed to protect thieves",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Samagi Jana Balawegaya Secretary General Parliament Member Ranjith Maddumabandara said that the people of the country tried to send the thieves in power home by struggling and marching.",
        "He said this while attending a press conference held at the office of the opposition leader in Colombo.",
        "Further, Member of Parliament Mr. Ranjith Maddumabandara expressed his views.",
        "A new president for this country was elected yesterday in parliament. First of all, I wish him well. I pray that he will get the strength to rebuild this country. We have to ask that the country's referendum was also represented in Parliament yesterday. The MPs in the Parliament today are the MPs who came forward in the 2020 elections under the prevailing atmosphere and according to the opinion of the people at that time. That opinion has changed today. Then we say that the opinion of the country is not reflected here. According to the opinion of the people of the country, the president who was appointed then fled this country. Most of this was done by the people who worked to appoint that president. Most of the MPs appointed with the President are in the Parliament.",
        "So we ask that the people of this country struggled, marched and protested to drive out the thieves. Now today the thieves have joined together and appointed one person. The people of this country expected a clean politics. That's why we prepared to go on a journey together with Mr. Sajith Premadasa, who has clean both hands, and Mr. Dallas Alahapperuma, who has clean hands. Our party did not spend even five cents on this. We need a president who acts according to the opinion of the people. What is the reason for these members of parliament to vote? Recovering the country from the flood? Or establish democracy in the country? According to what we heard, they have to fix the fire in their house. We are not against it. For their own safety. Get your vehicle permit. The MPs here have voted to stay in power."
      ],
